tip.text: Absolutely lovely setting in lush gardens, and absolutely lovely people! Great coffee, shakes, smoothies, and those chapati chips can get addictive!
Absolutely magical setting, with warm and friendly service. Basically the best undiscovered boutique hotel in town!
Perfectly executed, authentic German food (in a city where it's often easier to find better pho than schnitzel) on a beautiful corner with outdoor seating just across from the lake.
The menu alone (with its flavour diagram) is worth coming for to get a reference for how to understand cocktails. Bartenders clearly have passion, and are totally welcoming -- worth seeking out
Who knew you could have a wildly diverse journey all in desserts? From the first Southeast Asian-inspired surprise of pandan and coconut to the final chocolate/charcoal finale -- unforgettable
A real hidden gem -- could spend hours just lazing the day away in the quiet, tranquil beauty of this little oasis. Frequent (low-key) events keep things lively but chill.

venue.name: Brera Botanical Garden (Orto Botanico di Brera)

formattedAddress: Alzaia Naviglio Grande (Ripa di Porta Ticinese)

tip.text: It's possible to visit at night - minus the crowds, bathed in soft light, you'll likely have it all to yourself to soak in.
Seriously good burgers and hand-cut fries--an unexpected gem amid the usual mediocre food court options. Talho burger with chips patatas doces are tops!
Definitely the best food in Montserrat -- skip the school cafeteria experience by the train station and come for lovely Catalan cuisine. Set menus from around 27€ and wines from the region.
Good pizza (the owner is Italian!), good coffee, warm and friendly service in a laid-back setting: what more could you ask for?
Yes it's stuffy, yes it's hot and yes it's crowded--and it's exactly how fado should be. A literal temple to the art form, just oozing with soul. Go see fado at a museum if you want your air con.
Probably the best views over Girona (perfect for sunset) and an entrance to the walls.
We stumbled upon Casa Marieta like an oasis in a desert of closed restaurants on Christmas Day and found it bustling with locals, warm service, and Catalan food prepared with heart and soul!
Moroccan baked eggs are amazing! Love the Bloody Mary menu and as a bonus, the coffee is also great. A Sunday must!

tip.text: Unbelievably good and cheap. Get there before 8 and you can probably snag a table. After that, expect to wait, but it's worth it.
Can't beat the view, any time of day, and the pastas are made with love and fairly priced.
Quintessential Berlin nightlife experience! The expansive space gets crowded yet you still feel like you have the freedom to move. Great, welcoming vibe and mix of people!
Beers are great--their IPA is an aromatic delight and a nice change from the usual German beers. Food portions are ample and tasty!
